1
00:00:01,070 --> 00:00:03,680
(Episode 58)

2
00:00:25,700 --> 00:00:28,670
Why would Baek Ho's mother be here?

3
00:00:29,400 --> 00:00:30,840
You're the one who should stop.

4
00:00:32,100 --> 00:00:34,470
Of all the women out there,
you had to pick a side dish shop owner?

5
00:00:35,170 --> 00:00:36,980
I went to her place,
and their circumstances are pathetic.

6
00:00:37,280 --> 00:00:39,040
And her mother isn't all there, either.

7
00:00:39,610 --> 00:00:42,580
Knowing you went through that ordeal
because of me,

8
00:00:43,480 --> 00:00:44,820
I feel terrible.

9
00:00:52,290 --> 00:00:55,960
Don't tell me Tae Pyung just shoved
the affair photos in her face.

10
00:00:56,490 --> 00:00:58,500
So she's here to confront Chae Hwa Young?

11
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:00,100
The doors are closing.

12
00:01:03,740 --> 00:01:04,740
Aren't you getting on?

13
00:01:07,070 --> 00:01:08,110
Director Ma!

14
00:01:09,840 --> 00:01:10,840
Hong Ju?

15
00:01:11,640 --> 00:01:14,480
Ms. Han! What brings you here?

16
00:01:15,010 --> 00:01:16,050
Get in.

17
00:01:16,610 --> 00:01:17,620
Please, get in.

18
00:01:24,490 --> 00:01:27,860
Have you thought about what I said,
General Manager Kang?

19
00:01:30,860 --> 00:01:32,560
About you marrying my Seo Rin.

20
00:01:32,830 --> 00:01:35,200
She hasn't even gotten
her memory back yet.

21
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:37,800
I think this is a bit too rushed.

22
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:39,800
But how do you feel, General Manager Kang?

23
00:01:40,570 --> 00:01:42,070
About marrying my Seo Rin.

24
00:01:42,340 --> 00:01:44,510
If you just make up your mind,

25
00:01:45,010 --> 00:01:47,280
I'll take care of everything else.

26
00:01:51,880 --> 00:01:53,520
- Goodness.
- Gosh.

27
00:01:54,050 --> 00:01:56,190
Lawyer Kang Baek Ho, what brings you here?

28
00:01:56,790 --> 00:01:58,290
I'm here to see my brother.

29
00:02:00,020 --> 00:02:01,260
So...

30
00:02:01,260 --> 00:02:04,930
General Manager Kang's younger brother
is Lawyer Kang.

31
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:07,170
How do you know my brother?

32
00:02:15,140 --> 00:02:16,840
What kind of tea would you like, Ms. Han?

33
00:02:16,910 --> 00:02:19,510
Could you contact CEO Chae for me first?

34
00:02:19,740 --> 00:02:22,410
Ms. Han, you don't have to be
so formal with me.

35
00:02:22,910 --> 00:02:24,720
- Should I?
- Of course.

36
00:02:29,220 --> 00:02:31,960
Manager Lee, where is CEO Chae right now?

37
00:02:37,530 --> 00:02:39,630
Seo Rin should still be in the hotel.

38
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:42,470
What if she runs into Lawyer Kang?

39
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:54,550
- Ma'am, you have a visitor.
- A visitor?

40
00:03:01,690 --> 00:03:04,120
I'll let you two brothers catch up.

41
00:03:14,570 --> 00:03:17,340
Keep a close eye on Lawyer Kang Baek Ho...

42
00:03:17,340 --> 00:03:18,470
so he doesn't run into Seo Rin.

43
00:03:18,900 --> 00:03:21,240
- Yes, ma'am.
- And who is this visitor?

44
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:24,080
It's Lawyer Han Young Ja.

45
00:03:24,340 --> 00:03:25,640
Who did you say was here?

46
00:03:25,740 --> 00:03:27,280
Professor Kang Nam Bong's wife.

47
00:03:28,680 --> 00:03:31,020
You mean the woman who raised Jun Ho?

48
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:33,620
- Yes.
- What for?

49
00:03:34,690 --> 00:03:37,560
- Oh no. It can't be.
- I tried to stop you.

50
00:03:47,470 --> 00:03:48,700
Who did you say you wanted to see?

51
00:03:49,230 --> 00:03:50,400
Director Ma Seo Rin?

52
00:03:51,270 --> 00:03:53,100
- Why?
- I just need to ask her something.

53
00:03:53,370 --> 00:03:54,410
Like what?

54
00:03:54,410 --> 00:03:55,970
Can't you just get her for me?

55
00:03:56,310 --> 00:03:58,210
You can at least introduce us, can't you?

56
00:03:58,540 --> 00:03:59,680
I'm asking you, why?

57
00:03:59,740 --> 00:04:01,550
Why are you grilling me
with so many questions?

58
00:04:01,680 --> 00:04:03,310
Just let me see her.

59
00:04:04,080 --> 00:04:07,450
I can't just let you see her
without her permission.

60
00:04:07,820 --> 00:04:09,120
I'll ask her later.

61
00:04:09,450 --> 00:04:11,820
What is she, some kind of princess?

62
00:04:12,260 --> 00:04:13,730
She's impossible to get a meeting with.

63
00:04:14,130 --> 00:04:16,260
Why is everyone trying to keep me
from seeing Director Ma?

64
00:04:16,930 --> 00:04:18,360
This just makes me want
to meet her even more.

65
00:04:26,970 --> 00:04:28,870
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

66
00:04:30,380 --> 00:04:31,910
I'm sorry to have kept you waiting.

67
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:33,810
I know this is presumptuous,

68
00:04:34,210 --> 00:04:37,150
showing up unannounced like this.
I apologize.

69
00:04:37,450 --> 00:04:38,820
I haven't properly introduced myself.

70
00:04:44,890 --> 00:04:46,460
My name is Han Young Ja.

71
00:04:46,590 --> 00:04:48,790
I'm Professor Kang Nam Bong's wife.

72
00:04:52,060 --> 00:04:53,800
Yes, please have a seat.

73
00:04:59,170 --> 00:05:02,040
What was it you wanted to see me
about so suddenly?

74
00:05:02,210 --> 00:05:05,680
I'll get straight to the point.

75
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:07,610
My husband...

76
00:05:08,810 --> 00:05:13,520
I mean, Professor Kang.
He has some trauma from the accident.

77
00:05:14,390 --> 00:05:17,720
His anxiety seems to have gotten
much worse lately.

78
00:05:18,090 --> 00:05:20,460
So she's here to ask for a favor.

79
00:05:21,090 --> 00:05:22,490
I was worried for nothing.

80
00:05:22,890 --> 00:05:24,060
I can only imagine.

81
00:05:25,230 --> 00:05:28,730
Even if the victim was partially at fault,
someone still died.

82
00:05:28,830 --> 00:05:30,700
Technically, he was on his way...

83
00:05:30,700 --> 00:05:33,500
to resolve a Dream Project issue
when it happened.

84
00:05:34,370 --> 00:05:37,710
So you can't say the company is
entirely without fault.

85
00:05:38,740 --> 00:05:40,980
Being a lawyer,
you're quick to figure out the angles.

86
00:05:42,810 --> 00:05:47,820
My husband wouldn't dare bring this up,
so I'm stepping in myself.

87
00:05:47,950 --> 00:05:49,020
I suppose so.

88
00:05:49,390 --> 00:05:51,790
Professor Kang does have experience
with the reopening,

89
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:55,690
so it would make sense for him
to continue working on the Dream Project.

90
00:05:56,230 --> 00:05:57,800
I should have thought of that myself.

91
00:05:58,500 --> 00:06:02,330
I'll contact the university
to request their cooperation.

92
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:06,770
You have a very straightforward
way of doing things.

93
00:06:07,210 --> 00:06:08,810
I'm glad we're on the same page.

94
00:06:09,910 --> 00:06:14,310
I've been feeling terrible about
the professor's accident as well.

95
00:06:15,110 --> 00:06:19,020
In any case, this isn't a decision
I can make on my own.

96
00:06:19,250 --> 00:06:21,550
I'll be in touch in a few days.

97
00:06:21,750 --> 00:06:22,950
That would be great.

98
00:06:26,290 --> 00:06:27,290
Just a moment.

99
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:29,760
Lawyer Han.

100
00:06:32,800 --> 00:06:35,630
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

101
00:06:45,080 --> 00:06:47,910
Why did that woman come
to see Mom earlier?

102
00:06:49,050 --> 00:06:52,020
I'm guessing it was about the accident.

103
00:06:52,450 --> 00:06:53,450
The accident?

104
00:06:55,890 --> 00:06:59,420
You mean that car crash
on the way to Dream Resort?

105
00:07:00,220 --> 00:07:01,230
Wait a minute.

106
00:07:02,260 --> 00:07:04,000
You remember that car crash?

107
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:08,430
Remember it? No.
I found out by searching for it.

108
00:07:14,170 --> 00:07:18,540
What? You went to Dream Hotel
and met with CEO Chae?

109
00:07:18,810 --> 00:07:21,750
- Why? What for?
- Why else?

110
00:07:22,010 --> 00:07:23,610
It's because of your trauma.

111
00:07:24,150 --> 00:07:27,850
- And CEO Chae is partly responsible.
- What are you talking about?

112
00:07:28,150 --> 00:07:31,320
What does CEO Chae have to do with it?

113
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:32,590
She has everything to do with it.

114
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:37,060
You got into that accident on your way
to their company for a work issue.

115
00:07:37,530 --> 00:07:39,200
Anyway, just wait.

116
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:43,230
CEO Chae said she'd send
an official request to your university.

117
00:07:43,470 --> 00:07:45,900
If you keep working with Dream Hotel,

118
00:07:46,170 --> 00:07:48,040
it'll boost your confidence,

119
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:50,540
and then it could help you
overcome your trauma.

120
00:07:50,610 --> 00:07:53,240
- Why would you do something like that?
- Why do you think?

121
00:07:53,310 --> 00:07:54,310
I'm home.

122
00:07:54,380 --> 00:07:57,680
Strictly speaking, the company shares
some of the blame for your accident.

123
00:07:57,750 --> 00:08:00,080
Why are you meddling in things
you shouldn't?

124
00:08:00,220 --> 00:08:02,850
You were grading exams...

125
00:08:02,850 --> 00:08:05,060
when an issue made you leave
for Dream Resort.

126
00:08:05,120 --> 00:08:08,060
So you went to beg CEO Chae for a favor?
How humiliating!

127
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:11,130
Why do you always do things
without asking me first?

128
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:14,130
My goodness, honey.
Is this really worth getting angry over?

129
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:17,540
There was no need for you
to go begging to CEO Chae.

130
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:19,670
Who said anything about begging?

131
00:08:21,410 --> 00:08:23,040
Do you really think
I'm that kind of person?

132
00:08:23,670 --> 00:08:27,250
I went there to claim
what you're rightfully owed.

133
00:08:27,450 --> 00:08:28,850
I was demanding what's rightfully yours.

134
00:08:28,850 --> 00:08:30,550
What's rightfully mine?

135
00:08:30,980 --> 00:08:32,720
Have you no self-respect? Darn it.

136
00:08:34,890 --> 00:08:35,890
I cannot believe him.

137
00:08:36,290 --> 00:08:37,790
Is this really something
to get so angry over?

138
00:08:38,090 --> 00:08:39,090
Good grief.

139
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:42,190
What does self-respect have to do with it?

140
00:08:42,190 --> 00:08:43,260
Give me a break.

141
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:47,770
Dad's just on edge
because of what he's been through.

142
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:49,470
It's not that.

143
00:08:50,300 --> 00:08:53,400
It's because his ego was bruised
in front of a pretty woman.

144
00:08:54,140 --> 00:08:55,510
Men, I swear...

145
00:08:55,870 --> 00:08:58,840
They lose their heads over a pretty face.
My goodness...

146
00:09:01,910 --> 00:09:04,180
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

147
00:09:07,620 --> 00:09:09,420
By the way, Director Ma,

148
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:12,520
why didn't you show when you said
you'd meet me at the hospital?

149
00:09:12,820 --> 00:09:14,160
You were supposed to repay
your debt to me.

150
00:09:15,690 --> 00:09:18,860
Am I supposed to be grateful
that you let me be with Jun Ho?

151
00:09:19,860 --> 00:09:21,870
You must not know
because you can't remember...

152
00:09:21,870 --> 00:09:23,530
- Whatever.
- So...

153
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:26,670
Did you stand me up on purpose
just to mess with me?

154
00:09:27,170 --> 00:09:28,170
Maybe I did.

155
00:09:30,070 --> 00:09:33,010
So she didn't show on purpose.

156
00:09:34,810 --> 00:09:36,410
I think I overdid it.
My head is starting to hurt.

157
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:40,420
If my mom asks for me,
tell her I went home.

158
00:09:47,090 --> 00:09:49,060
Since she doesn't remember Jun Ho,

159
00:09:49,790 --> 00:09:51,400
I guess she's not lying about her amnesia.

160
00:09:54,170 --> 00:09:55,970
But she's still as bratty as ever.

161
00:10:07,110 --> 00:10:08,650
I miss my mom.

162
00:10:12,580 --> 00:10:14,150
I don't even have a single picture of her.

163
00:10:15,590 --> 00:10:16,850
I miss her so much.

164
00:10:17,690 --> 00:10:18,720
My mom...

165
00:10:22,690 --> 00:10:26,700
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

166
00:10:50,890 --> 00:10:52,390
Hello, this is Suk Hee's Side Dish Shop.

167
00:10:52,620 --> 00:10:53,860
I'd like...

168
00:10:54,760 --> 00:10:57,830
I'd like to place a lunch box order.

169
00:10:57,830 --> 00:10:58,900
Yes, and what's the delivery address?

170
00:10:58,960 --> 00:11:02,830
Please deliver 100 lunches every Monday
to the Happy Children's Home.

171
00:11:02,930 --> 00:11:04,140
A 100?

172
00:11:04,870 --> 00:11:06,270
Every single week?

173
00:11:07,410 --> 00:11:10,310
To prevent no-shows,

174
00:11:10,510 --> 00:11:12,610
we require a 50 percent deposit upfront.

175
00:11:13,110 --> 00:11:15,580
- I should let you know that's our policy.
- I understand.

176
00:11:16,010 --> 00:11:19,280
I've already transferred
a full month's payment to your account.

177
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:21,190
Wait, are you serious?

178
00:11:22,220 --> 00:11:23,290
Check.

179
00:11:26,990 --> 00:11:29,860
- It's here! The money's here.
- You really did!

180
00:11:30,490 --> 00:11:32,230
- Thank you.
- Wait.

181
00:11:32,230 --> 00:11:33,630
What is your name?

182
00:11:35,970 --> 00:11:39,540
- Hey, what's the name on the deposit?
- It says "Tok Hee."

183
00:11:40,140 --> 00:11:41,870
What? Tok Hee?

184
00:11:42,470 --> 00:11:44,280
You mean the Tok Hee
that Mom is always talking about?

185
00:11:44,640 --> 00:11:45,840
Tok Hee is pretty.

186
00:11:46,280 --> 00:11:49,680
- Tok Hee is sick.
- Either way, this Tok Hee is a lifesaver.

187
00:11:50,680 --> 00:11:51,680
You can say that again.

188
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:57,320
Mom, we're about to get really busy.
You think you can handle it?

189
00:11:57,460 --> 00:12:00,120
Suk Hee is good. She's good at everything.

190
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:02,330
Jang Mi is pretty.

191
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:08,000
Mom.

192
00:12:08,870 --> 00:12:09,870
My mom.

193
00:12:10,870 --> 00:12:12,070
Just wait a little longer.

194
00:12:12,740 --> 00:12:14,870
Seo Rin will wake up. I know she will.

195
00:12:15,510 --> 00:12:17,340
I'll bring her to you, Mom.

196
00:12:17,940 --> 00:12:20,640
So please, just wait a little longer.
Okay?

197
00:12:21,480 --> 00:12:23,980
My mom. My sweet mom.

198
00:12:29,390 --> 00:12:32,490
Jang Mi? Jang Mi is pretty.

199
00:12:32,690 --> 00:12:33,720
What? Mom?

200
00:12:33,790 --> 00:12:36,560
Jang Mi is pretty. I miss Jang Mi.

201
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:41,670
It's Jang Mi! Jang Mi is pretty!

202
00:12:42,230 --> 00:12:44,470
Mom, Jang Mi is in the hospital
right now, remember?

203
00:12:44,540 --> 00:12:47,570
No, that's Jang Mi. She's here.

204
00:12:47,640 --> 00:12:48,970
I want to see Jang Mi.

205
00:12:49,570 --> 00:12:50,770
Jang Mi is so pretty.

206
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:54,410
- I want to see Jang Mi.
- Mom.

207
00:12:55,180 --> 00:12:56,650
I miss Jang Mi.

208
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:05,720
Mom.

209
00:13:06,990 --> 00:13:08,790
You always know it's me, Mom.

210
00:13:09,630 --> 00:13:11,460
You recognized Seo Rin right away, too.

211
00:13:12,260 --> 00:13:14,370
Mom, I'm so sorry.

212
00:13:15,230 --> 00:13:17,130
I'm sorry I can't be there with you.

213
00:13:24,980 --> 00:13:27,810
You are indeed a gentleman
for keeping your promise.

214
00:13:29,080 --> 00:13:30,080
Baek Ho,

215
00:13:30,380 --> 00:13:31,820
you must have been really popular
back in school.

216
00:13:33,180 --> 00:13:35,490
With a face like this,
it'd be a lie to say no.

217
00:13:37,890 --> 00:13:41,530
Baek Ho, I know you're going through a lot
right now because of Oh Jang Mi.

218
00:13:42,260 --> 00:13:43,690
That's why when you're struggling,

219
00:13:44,330 --> 00:13:46,330
I want to be by your side to support you.

220
00:13:46,660 --> 00:13:48,600
I appreciate the offer, but I'm fine.

221
00:13:49,470 --> 00:13:50,630
Why?

222
00:13:50,900 --> 00:13:52,640
You never know what the future holds.

223
00:13:53,040 --> 00:13:55,540
I might be able to help you again,
just like last time.

224
00:13:57,540 --> 00:14:00,310
By the way, has Ma Seo Rin
gotten her memory back?

225
00:14:00,640 --> 00:14:02,210
Why do you keep asking about Seo Rin?

226
00:14:03,210 --> 00:14:06,350
Don't tell me you're interested in her,
are you, Baek Ho?

227
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:10,050
What? No, what are you talking about?
Can't I even just ask?

228
00:14:10,150 --> 00:14:11,390
Do you have any idea...

229
00:14:11,660 --> 00:14:13,390
how often you bring up Seo Rin
when we're together?

230
00:14:14,460 --> 00:14:16,260
I have?

231
00:14:16,530 --> 00:14:18,530
You're not actually interested in me.

232
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:20,970
You're just trying to find something out
about Oh Jang Mi, aren't you?

233
00:14:21,870 --> 00:14:23,530
I'm a lot sharper than you think.

234
00:14:24,740 --> 00:14:25,740
Is that right?

235
00:14:27,440 --> 00:14:29,310
Goodness, look at the time.

236
00:14:29,870 --> 00:14:33,210
Anyway, I kept my promise.
I'm going to head out.

237
00:14:33,540 --> 00:14:35,580
- I already took care of the check.
- Wait.

238
00:14:36,010 --> 00:14:37,080
Where are you going?

239
00:14:37,620 --> 00:14:38,950
You're not even going to give me a ride?

240
00:14:45,490 --> 00:14:48,460
- Grandfather.
- Yes, of course, Seo Rin.

241
00:14:49,560 --> 00:14:54,030
I have a special gift just for you.

242
00:14:54,930 --> 00:14:56,730
You do? What is it?

243
00:14:57,170 --> 00:14:59,340
What do you think?
It's a building in Gangnam.

244
00:15:00,140 --> 00:15:01,170
A gift for my dear Seo Rin.

245
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:04,840
What did you just say?

246
00:15:04,940 --> 00:15:06,040
(Building Gift Agreement)

247
00:15:06,180 --> 00:15:09,310
Wait, so that wasn't a gift
for our anniversary?

248
00:15:11,050 --> 00:15:12,250
Thank you, Father.

249
00:15:12,820 --> 00:15:16,920
No one could ever love
Seo Rin more than you do.

250
00:15:18,190 --> 00:15:22,290
But, darling, our Hong Ju
is your daughter too.

251
00:15:22,530 --> 00:15:23,890
Isn't there anything for Hong Ju?

252
00:15:24,900 --> 00:15:27,100
Instead of congratulating
and being happy for her,

253
00:15:27,560 --> 00:15:29,700
why must you be so crass?

254
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:32,970
Still, if Hong Ju is the only one
left empty-handed,

255
00:15:33,770 --> 00:15:35,140
it's a little upsetting.

256
00:15:35,210 --> 00:15:39,410
Seo Rin's car accident
scared me half to death.

257
00:15:39,740 --> 00:15:42,310
This is a gift to show
how happy I am that you're safe.

258
00:15:43,480 --> 00:15:44,720
So how are you, Seo Rin?

259
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:47,850
Are your memories slowly coming back?

260
00:15:49,420 --> 00:15:52,460
Yes, of course, Grandfather.
It's coming back bit by bit.

261
00:15:56,330 --> 00:15:57,560
Grandfather, thank you!

262
00:15:57,560 --> 00:15:59,900
- Thank you so much.
- Oh, of course!

263
00:15:59,900 --> 00:16:01,800
Your memory is all back now!

264
00:16:02,030 --> 00:16:03,870
Thank goodness! Thank you!

265
00:16:06,640 --> 00:16:08,510
Is her memory really back?

266
00:16:14,210 --> 00:16:15,850
Darn it, I can't stand her.

267
00:16:17,350 --> 00:16:20,780
Mom, Director Ma's memory isn't back yet.

268
00:16:21,690 --> 00:16:23,720
And she has the nerve to pretend
in front of Father that it has.

269
00:16:25,460 --> 00:16:28,590
This can't be happening.
I'm so furious. Unbelievable.

270
00:16:28,760 --> 00:16:32,500
Seriously, when will he give us our cut?
What's taking him so long?

271
00:16:32,700 --> 00:16:34,700
What's the point of you being married
to the Chairman...

272
00:16:34,970 --> 00:16:36,270
if we're still completely broke?

273
00:16:42,370 --> 00:16:44,710
Jang Mi, I'm here.

274
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:47,010
You can hear my voice, can't you?

275
00:16:49,080 --> 00:16:51,650
They say you can still hear
even when you're unconscious.

276
00:16:55,590 --> 00:16:56,820
I love you, Jang Mi.

277
00:16:57,920 --> 00:16:58,920
You know how I feel, right?

278
00:17:04,600 --> 00:17:05,900
If I'd known the accident...

279
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:08,230
would leave you like this,

280
00:17:10,130 --> 00:17:12,100
I would've told you all the things...

281
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:14,810
I always held back.

282
00:17:18,380 --> 00:17:19,380
I'm filled with regret,

283
00:17:21,610 --> 00:17:22,610
so much regret.

284
00:17:27,450 --> 00:17:28,450
I'm so sorry,

285
00:17:30,920 --> 00:17:32,090
and I love you, Jang Mi.

286
00:17:40,330 --> 00:17:43,130
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

287
00:17:43,200 --> 00:17:45,640
After I put Jun Ho in charge
of the Dream Project...

288
00:17:45,640 --> 00:17:47,640
as the general manager,

289
00:17:47,770 --> 00:17:49,870
I'm not being too uninvolved, am I?

290
00:17:50,010 --> 00:17:51,980
Are you worried about
General Manager Kang Jun Ho?

291
00:17:52,680 --> 00:17:54,410
I'm not worried about Jun Ho.

292
00:17:55,150 --> 00:17:57,610
When he challenged one of my plans,

293
00:17:58,020 --> 00:18:00,320
I saw for myself what he's capable of.

294
00:18:01,620 --> 00:18:04,390
But to the other executives
he'll be working with,

295
00:18:04,720 --> 00:18:07,160
Jun Ho still has to prove himself.

296
00:18:07,930 --> 00:18:09,860
I'm worried they might be
disrespectful to him.

297
00:18:11,300 --> 00:18:14,930
At times like this,
I have the strongest urge...

298
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:18,700
to just announce that
Kang Jun Ho is my son.

299
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:21,510
What if we expedite the wedding
for Seo Rin and General Manager Kang?

300
00:18:21,770 --> 00:18:23,470
Yes, I was thinking the same thing.

301
00:18:24,070 --> 00:18:27,180
I want you to leak this to your sources.

302
00:18:27,810 --> 00:18:30,450
Say that Chairman Ma
and I have handpicked...

303
00:18:30,450 --> 00:18:32,550
General Manager Kang Jun Ho
as Seo Rin's match.

304
00:18:33,250 --> 00:18:36,250
That way, no one will dare
to disrespect Jun Ho.

305
00:18:37,190 --> 00:18:38,290
Yes, ma'am.

306
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:40,260
Ever since Seo Rin got hurt,

307
00:18:40,690 --> 00:18:43,230
the Chairman has become
even more doting on her,

308
00:18:43,730 --> 00:18:46,000
so I need to take this chance
and push their wedding...

309
00:18:46,830 --> 00:18:48,500
through as quickly as possible.

310
00:18:50,130 --> 00:18:51,200
Understood.

311
00:18:55,770 --> 00:18:56,840
Hello.

312
00:19:02,380 --> 00:19:03,480
Congratulations.

313
00:19:17,060 --> 00:19:20,260
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

314
00:19:23,370 --> 00:19:25,300
Director Ma, is it true?

315
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:27,800
What is?

316
00:19:28,670 --> 00:19:31,740
Since everyone else at work already knows,
I'll just ask.

317
00:19:32,610 --> 00:19:33,810
I hear your wedding...

318
00:19:33,880 --> 00:19:36,510
to the General Manager Kang
is right around the corner.

319
00:19:36,580 --> 00:19:38,550
What? Me?

320
00:19:39,280 --> 00:19:41,990
Goodness. How can you be the only one
who doesn't know?

321
00:19:42,220 --> 00:19:44,150
They say the CEO Chae is
rushing your marriage...

322
00:19:44,150 --> 00:19:45,260
to the General Manager Kang.

323
00:19:45,490 --> 00:19:48,630
My mom is arranging my marriage
to General Manager Kang Jun Ho?

324
00:19:50,890 --> 00:19:51,900
No way.

325
00:19:52,460 --> 00:19:55,000
Baek Ho, what am I going to do?

326
00:20:06,840 --> 00:20:09,480
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

327
00:20:10,050 --> 00:20:11,180
What is it?

328
00:20:11,680 --> 00:20:12,950
Can't you see I'm working?

329
00:20:17,120 --> 00:20:20,290
- What's going on?
- Are the office rumors true?

330
00:20:20,720 --> 00:20:21,760
What rumor?

331
00:20:22,060 --> 00:20:24,560
Is it true you picked General Manager Kang
to be my husband?

332
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:27,760
And that you're pushing for us
to get married right away?

333
00:20:28,170 --> 00:20:29,430
Is that all this is about?

334
00:20:30,130 --> 00:20:32,370
Before your accident, you were thrilled...

335
00:20:32,370 --> 00:20:34,300
when I allowed you
to marry General Manager Kang.

336
00:20:34,610 --> 00:20:38,240
What? So Seo Rin was in love with him.

337
00:20:39,010 --> 00:20:41,040
What in the world is wrong
with your memory?

338
00:20:41,910 --> 00:20:44,480
You pretend your memory's back
for Grandfather,

339
00:20:44,950 --> 00:20:46,720
but for General Manager Kang,
whom you were so crazy about,

340
00:20:46,980 --> 00:20:48,890
you seem to have completely forgotten.

341
00:20:49,920 --> 00:20:50,990
I don't understand it myself.

342
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:55,130
Even looking at his picture on my phone,
I can't remember a thing.

343
00:20:55,430 --> 00:20:58,200
You used to chase Kang Jun Ho constantly
because you liked him so much.

344
00:21:00,200 --> 00:21:03,970
Just get ready to marry
General Manager Kang Jun Ho soon.

345
00:21:04,170 --> 00:21:05,800
No way. I don't want to.

346
00:21:06,170 --> 00:21:07,170
What?

347
00:21:08,240 --> 00:21:10,210
You have to marry Kang Jun Ho.

348
00:21:10,740 --> 00:21:14,510
Do you think you can find another man
as capable and respectable as him?

349
00:21:14,910 --> 00:21:16,780
You need a man like that by your side...

350
00:21:17,350 --> 00:21:19,820
if you want to properly grow
into your role as successor.

351
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:22,390
I'm not getting married right now.

352
00:21:22,850 --> 00:21:23,850
Why not?

353
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:26,020
I don't want to be tied down.

354
00:21:26,160 --> 00:21:27,690
So call off this marriage talk.

355
00:21:28,630 --> 00:21:30,490
I'm still recovering from the accident.

356
00:21:30,560 --> 00:21:32,660
Marriage is too much right now, isn't it?

357
00:21:32,760 --> 00:21:35,200
You just do as I say.

358
00:21:35,530 --> 00:21:37,700
I'm setting you up for a perfect life.

359
00:21:38,770 --> 00:21:40,970
Everything I'm doing is for your own good.

360
00:21:41,170 --> 00:21:43,510
So don't argue and do as I say.

361
00:21:43,640 --> 00:21:45,510
I made it perfectly clear
that I won't get married now.

362
00:21:46,540 --> 00:21:48,780
So this must have been
what Seo Rin's life was always like.

363
00:21:49,580 --> 00:21:51,450
She could have anything she wanted,

364
00:21:52,050 --> 00:21:53,780
but her life was completely controlled
by Chae Hwa Young.

365
00:21:57,520 --> 00:21:58,520
Ma Seo Rin.

366
00:22:02,190 --> 00:22:04,660
She was so crazy about Jun Ho,
always chasing him around.

367
00:22:05,500 --> 00:22:09,970
Even with amnesia from the accident,
how could she reject him so strongly?

368
00:22:11,170 --> 00:22:14,470
Feelings of love don't just disappear
like that.

369
00:22:16,610 --> 00:22:18,810
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

370
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:20,780
General Manager Kang, is it true?

371
00:22:21,140 --> 00:22:22,150
What are you referring to?

372
00:22:22,480 --> 00:22:24,480
That the Chairman and CEO Chae...

373
00:22:24,480 --> 00:22:27,150
are fast-tracking your wedding
to Director Ma.

374
00:22:27,720 --> 00:22:29,590
That rumor is all over the office.

375
00:22:30,420 --> 00:22:31,690
So that's why...

376
00:22:32,120 --> 00:22:35,830
everyone's changing
their tune and being so friendly.

377
00:22:35,930 --> 00:22:37,960
They're saying your promotion
to General Manager...

378
00:22:38,230 --> 00:22:40,760
was all with this marriage in mind.

379
00:22:41,100 --> 00:22:42,900
Now it all makes sense.

380
00:22:42,900 --> 00:22:46,340
I've noticed a different vibe
when you're with Director Ma lately.

381
00:22:46,740 --> 00:22:48,840
I knew it.

382
00:22:48,840 --> 00:22:49,940
Team Leader Jin.

383
00:22:50,940 --> 00:22:53,640
If you'll jump to conclusions like others,
be my guest.

384
00:22:54,380 --> 00:22:56,750
I couldn't care less
about rumors like that.

385
00:22:58,120 --> 00:23:00,420
I sure CEO Chae's behind it all.

386
00:23:00,420 --> 00:23:01,420
Why?

387
00:23:01,850 --> 00:23:04,860
It wouldn't hurt to just play along,
you know.

388
00:23:07,060 --> 00:23:10,530
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

389
00:23:14,500 --> 00:23:15,900
I still haven't found the evidence,

390
00:23:16,630 --> 00:23:19,700
and at this rate,
I'm going to lose Baek Ho forever.

391
00:23:20,240 --> 00:23:21,640
What do I do?

392
00:23:21,640 --> 00:23:23,410
How could I marry
General Manager Kang Jun Ho?

393
00:23:24,370 --> 00:23:25,710
No, that can't happen.

394
00:23:25,840 --> 00:23:28,650
He's just someone I look up to and admire.

395
00:23:28,950 --> 00:23:30,510
We are definitely not lovers.

396
00:23:56,910 --> 00:24:01,240
If I try to find the evidence Seo Rin hid,
it'll take way too long.

397
00:24:02,050 --> 00:24:03,250
For now, I'll use this video...

398
00:24:04,010 --> 00:24:05,880
to tell Grandfather everything.

399
00:24:19,600 --> 00:24:24,000
It's going to break Grandfather's heart
when he finds out the truth.

400
00:24:24,570 --> 00:24:26,400
Especially with Seo Rin in this condition.

401
00:24:27,470 --> 00:24:29,270
No. Still, I have to tell him.

402
00:24:29,940 --> 00:24:31,680
Taking down Chae Hwa Young comes first.

403
00:24:32,680 --> 00:24:35,910
Seo Rin, you're a million miles away.
Go on, eat.

404
00:24:36,050 --> 00:24:37,050
Pardon?

405
00:24:37,810 --> 00:24:38,820
Right.

406
00:24:44,420 --> 00:24:47,390
I still can't stomach those eyeballs.

407
00:24:47,820 --> 00:24:49,730
Just eat your food.

408
00:24:50,390 --> 00:24:53,530
- Eat up, Seo Rin. Okay?
- Okay.

409
00:25:01,370 --> 00:25:02,370
Seo Rin.

410
00:25:02,670 --> 00:25:04,810
I thought you loved fish eyeballs.
Why are you...

411
00:25:16,290 --> 00:25:17,450
Sorry, this is important.

412
00:25:20,820 --> 00:25:21,930
Hello, Reporter Kim.

413
00:25:23,090 --> 00:25:24,090
Excuse me?

414
00:25:25,600 --> 00:25:29,330
I've been chosen as one of the top three
female CEOs in Asia?

415
00:25:32,500 --> 00:25:34,940
Great. When will the article be published?

416
00:25:35,610 --> 00:25:38,240
Next week? I see.

417
00:25:38,910 --> 00:25:41,280
Thank you for making this happen,
Reporter Kim.

418
00:25:41,880 --> 00:25:43,780
I'll have to treat you to a meal sometime.

419
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:46,880
Okay. Manager Lee will give you a call.

420
00:25:47,520 --> 00:25:48,520
Talk to you then.

421
00:25:50,750 --> 00:25:53,860
Would you believe that, Hwa Young?
You actually got picked for something.

422
00:25:54,360 --> 00:25:55,860
Congratulations, ma'am.

423
00:25:56,260 --> 00:25:57,590
Do you really mean that?

424
00:25:58,160 --> 00:26:00,230
You're not just saying that, are you?

425
00:26:01,160 --> 00:26:02,230
Of course not.

426
00:26:02,900 --> 00:26:05,800
Let's issue a company press release
first thing tomorrow.

427
00:26:05,800 --> 00:26:07,070
Good. Do that.

428
00:26:08,040 --> 00:26:09,040
Father.

429
00:26:09,610 --> 00:26:12,840
They named me one of the most admired
female CEOs.

430
00:26:13,280 --> 00:26:15,880
That's some good news for the company
for a change.

431
00:26:16,210 --> 00:26:17,380
Congratulations, Mom.

432
00:26:17,910 --> 00:26:20,380
You've been going through a lot,
so this must be a nice boost.

433
00:26:21,220 --> 00:26:24,490
Grandfather, Mom hasn't even been
getting paid recently.

434
00:26:24,650 --> 00:26:25,890
We should start paying her again.

435
00:26:25,890 --> 00:26:28,760
Who's giving out this award, anyway?

436
00:26:29,390 --> 00:26:31,490
You didn't just buy it, did you?

437
00:26:32,260 --> 00:26:36,400
A lot of people just pay
for those awards these days.

438
00:26:36,500 --> 00:26:37,930
Shut up, Yeom San Wol.

439
00:26:38,270 --> 00:26:42,070
She's right, ma'am.
How can you rain on her parade like that?

440
00:26:42,370 --> 00:26:44,210
It's an award
from the Business Leaders Association.

441
00:26:44,470 --> 00:26:46,040
Don't talk about things
you don't know about.

442
00:26:46,040 --> 00:26:47,180
Fine, I was just saying.

443
00:26:47,380 --> 00:26:50,180
You should apologize to my mother.

444
00:26:57,490 --> 00:26:58,490
Chae Hwa Young.

445
00:26:58,790 --> 00:27:00,720
This is the last act of kindness
you'll get from me.

446
00:27:01,420 --> 00:27:04,630
Because soon you'll be thrown out of here,
and your life will be over.

447
00:27:04,890 --> 00:27:05,930
So you'd better be ready.

448
00:27:08,060 --> 00:27:11,000
CEO Chae, after we finish eating,

449
00:27:11,200 --> 00:27:12,800
I'd like a word with you in the study.

450
00:27:13,400 --> 00:27:14,440
Yes, Father.

451
00:27:18,840 --> 00:27:21,110
I heard it was going to be
published in a current affairs magazine.

452
00:27:21,780 --> 00:27:22,780
So it seems.

453
00:27:23,350 --> 00:27:27,450
I suppose this is the reward
for all my hard work.

454
00:27:28,520 --> 00:27:32,220
It's all thanks to you
for recognizing my potential.

455
00:27:35,430 --> 00:27:39,000
Thirty years ago,
I brought Dong Seok's child...

456
00:27:39,430 --> 00:27:41,660
and came into this house.

457
00:27:42,730 --> 00:27:46,870
To this day, I have given my entire heart
and soul to Dream Hotel.

458
00:27:48,910 --> 00:27:50,670
Dong Seok, that fool...

459
00:27:52,110 --> 00:27:54,910
Right... CEO Chae...

460
00:27:55,680 --> 00:27:57,610
What was that woman's name again?

461
00:27:58,110 --> 00:28:00,050
The one Dong Seok was so taken with.

462
00:28:01,890 --> 00:28:03,290
Jung Suk Hee?

463
00:28:10,230 --> 00:28:12,030
Suk Hee is good at this.

464
00:28:14,200 --> 00:28:17,030
Suk Hee made the japchae.

465
00:28:24,310 --> 00:28:27,080
You mean Jung Suk Hee, right?

466
00:28:28,140 --> 00:28:31,280
I'm going to tell Grandfather everything.

467
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:56,370
(The First Man)

468
00:28:56,440 --> 00:28:58,980
My mom's way too beautiful
not to have a boyfriend.

469
00:28:59,140 --> 00:29:01,080
Her boyfriend will likely get her flowers,

470
00:29:01,080 --> 00:29:02,680
so maybe I should get her some jewelry?

471
00:29:02,850 --> 00:29:05,450
I figured out a way
to stick it to CEO Chae.

472
00:29:05,620 --> 00:29:08,690
This came for you, ma'am.
I picked it up out front.

473
00:29:09,090 --> 00:29:10,720
"Kang Nam Bong?"

474
00:29:10,720 --> 00:29:12,220
Who's Professor Kang Nam Bong?

475
00:29:12,620 --> 00:29:13,860
Is he really your boyfriend?

476
00:29:15,230 --> 00:29:17,630
- My gosh!
- Why would you clean that up?

477
00:29:18,190 --> 00:29:19,500
You're not Seo Rin, are you?

478
00:29:23,730 --> 00:29:25,770
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
